What is IAM?

IAM controls authentication and authorization in AWS.

Authentication:
Who are you?

Authorization:
What can you access?

IAM Components:

Users
Individual identities.

Example:
Arul
Kumar
Developer1
Groups

Collection of users.

Example:
Developers
Admins
Testers
Policies

JSON documents defining permissions.

Example:

{
 "Effect":"Allow",
 "Action":"ec2:StartInstances",
 "Resource":"*"
}
Roles

Temporary permissions assigned to AWS services.

Example:

EC2 → Access S3

No access keys required.

IAM Best Practices
Never use Root Account daily
Enable MFA
Follow Least Privilege Principle
Rotate Credentials
Use IAM Roles
Real-Time Scenario

Developer needs EC2 access.

Wrong:

AdministratorAccess

Correct:

Allow only EC2 permissions
